# Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge
We as members, contributors, and maintainers pledge to make participation in SentinelShell a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity or expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

We pledge to act and interact in ways that contribute to an open, welcoming, diverse, inclusive, and healthy community.

---

## Our Standards
Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment:

- Demonstrating empathy and kindness  
- Giving and receiving constructive feedback  
- Accepting responsibility and apologizing for mistakes  
- Focusing on what is best for the community  
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints  

Examples of unacceptable behavior:

- Harassment or intimidation  
- Discrimination or derogatory comments  
- Personal attacks  
- Publishing others' private information  
- Other conduct deemed inappropriate by maintainers  

---

## Enforcement Responsibilities
Project maintainers are responsible for:

- Clarifying standards  
- Enforcing appropriate behavior  
- Communicating moderation decisions when needed  

---

## Scope
This Code of Conduct applies:

- Within project spaces  
- On GitHub issues, PRs, discussions  
- In community channels related to the project  

---

## Enforcement
Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported privately to the project maintainer.

The maintainer will:

- Review all reports  
- Maintain confidentiality  
- Take appropriate action  

---

